title: Barney's Big Race
description: Inspired by a hot-rod in Mel's dad's garage, Barney helps the kids make their own magical hot rod-style race cars! When Mel gets frustrated that she keeps losing the race, Barney helps her realize there's more to racing than just winning.

title: Dances with Goblins
description: David can't agree on what to play, so the kids end up playing different games. Barney has a hard time keeping up with both games. Silly chaos ensues, and David is reminded that it's important to consider others' perspectives, too.

title: A Big Sad
description: After Vivie reads a sad story with her Nonna, Barney helps her embrace that it's okay to be sad sometimes. After feeling OK sitting in her sadness for a bit, Vivie comes up with a happy ending for the story.

title: Big, Bigger, Best
description: David feels like he's too small to do the all things his big brother can do, so Barney makes him super-sized. But throughout his super-sized adventures David realizes the importance of loving himself just as he is.

title: Billy's Intro
description: Billy takes us on a tour all around the park while riding his scooter! Follow along as he shows off some of his coolest moves.

title: Anger
description: Mel gets angry after accidentally crashing her toy plane into a tree. Barney helps Mel find healthy ways to express her anger and calm down -- and together, they fix her plane.

title: Check in on Your Body
description: When David asks Barney to play, Barney accidentally forgets to listen to his body and plays straight through his daily nap! He feels very sleepy and David helps Barney check in on his body. After a brief snooze Barney is ready to play again!

title: Missing Mel
description: Mel breaks her arm and is away from the park while she gets a cast. David really misses her, so Barney creates magical games to help David and Vivie do something nice for Mel for when she gets back.

title: Here if You Need Me
description: Mel tries to swing all the way across the monkey bars without any help. Barney lets Mel know he's there just in case she needs him. After a few tries, Mel makes it, and lets Barney know that it was because she knew he was there that she could do it.

title: Nature Chat
description: During a picnic in the park, Mel isn't being considerate of the environment around her. Barney transforms the kids into butterflies who can talk to the plants and animals. Mel learns it's important to respect and be a caretaker of nature.

title: Worth the Wait
description: Mel is frustrated that her arm isn't as strong as it used to be after she gets her cast off, so Barney whips up an adventure in the enchanted forest that helps her realize that it's okay for some things to take time.

title: One Ripe Tomato
description: When Vivie disagrees with her friends about who gets to use a ripe garden tomato, Barney creates space for everyone to share their ideas. Vivie realizes it's important to share and they use the tomato to make a pizza everyone can enjoy.

title: Barney's Intro
description: Barney the purple dinosaur introduces himself and takes us on a tour of the super-dee-super park! He dances, demonstrates how to take a Barney Breath, and shows off some of his fun Barney magic!

title: Practice Makes Purple
description: When Vivie discovers she's not amazing at soccer the first time she tries, she thinks she'll never be good at it. Barney creates fantastiical practice drills to help Vivie learn how practice can help her get better.

title: Save the Garden
description: Determined to save the community garden, Barney and the kids go on a magical adventure where they become butterflies, and help a little ladybug with a big problem. They ultimately learn that doing small things can affect big change!

title: I Lovey You
description: Barney's magic creates a nighttime adventure in the park, but David is scared of the dark. Barney becomes a giant glowing action figure to help David calm down so he can stay and play with his friends.

title: Drawing Attention
description: Vivie wants to show Nonna her special chalk drawing, but everyone's attention is on Mel's cast so Vivie fakes an injury to get attention too. When her plan falls through, Barney helps Vivie learn the value in speaking up for what she needs.

title: Mel's Greatest Treasure
description: Mel is on a quest to find a special treasure and accidentally makes a big mess in the park. Barney creates a magical adventure where Mel learns it's important to clean up and care for a place that's special to you and your community.

title: Sharing
description: Mel is upset that Vivie and Baby Bop won't share the swings with her. Barney encourages Mel to sing about her frustration -- but when Barney asks Mel to share her microphone, Mel realizes that it's okay to wait to share until you're ready.

title: The Castaway Crew
description: When Mel grows frustrated with the things she can't do while wearing a cast, Barney creates an imaginative game for the kids to play. Throughout the game, Mel learns to embrace her abilities with the help of a fantastical robot arm.

title: Make It Myself
description: When Vivie's newly-built sandcastle is accidentally destroyed, Barney offers to help her rebuild it using a little magic, but Vivie wants to do it all by herself. Together, they enjoy the process of constructing a new sandcastle from scratch.

title: Team Mateys
description: When Mel's pretzel is eaten by a pigeon, Barney creates a high-seas adventure to find another, but it goes awry when Captain Mel doesn't listen to her crew. Mel realizes it's important to listen to others when you're working as a team.

title: The Brave Truth
description: When Vivie accidentally breaks Mel's toy airplane, she's afraid to admit it. Barney creates magical knight and castle play to help Vivie feel brave enough to tell Mel the truth.

title: Baby Bop's Intro
description: Baby Bop is playing a game of hide and seek behind the Barney Bench! With a little Barney magic, she shows off a couple of her dress-up costumes and skills, all while celebrating her fabulous self.

title: That Dizzy Feeling
description: Vivie and Barney roll down the hill, again and again. When Vivie feels dizzy, she reveals that she's nervous to speak up about it because she doesn't want to ruin the fun. Barney thanks Vivie for being honest and they pick another game to play!

title: The Big Spill
description: Vivie is overcome with feelings of anger after a pigeon messes up her painting. Barney and the kids play Pirates and the Sea Queen to help de-escalate Vivie's anger and learn healthy ways to manage big feelings.

title: David the Hero
description: David's feeling too quiet to play heroes the same way as Mel and Vivie. Barney helps Mel and Vivie recognize that there's value in all different styles of play and David's chosen power of quiet observation ends up saving the day.

title: The Floor is Grape Jelly
description: When David is frustrated to be called home early to help with his baby sister, Barney creates a magical game where David is reminded how good it feels to help others. He leaves the park excited to help out as a big brother.

title: Little by Little
description: David gets scared to go down the high slide. Barney comforts David and shows him how to take it step by step until he feels ready to try the slide.

title: The Great Grateful Scavenger Hunt
description: When Mel's in a bad mood, she has a hard time finding the 'happy' in anything. Barney's magical scavenger hunt leads Mel to discover that searching for and focusing on things you're grateful for can make you feel better.

title: Red Light Stop, Green Light Go
description: Mel keeps trying to do a cool scooter trick and doesn't want to rest until she gets it right, but Mel pushes her body too far. Barney and Billy help Mel learn to listen to what her body is feeling and why it's important to do so.
